<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>According to <a href="http://manual.phpdoc.org/HTMLframesConverter/default/phpDocumentor/tutorial_tags.param.pkg.html">phpDocumentor</a>, the correct format of @param is:</p>

<pre class="literal">
@param datatype $paramname description
</pre>

<p>There are some instances in the codebase where the datatype is omitted or the terms are out of order (i.e. @param $foo string)</p>

<p>For example, run this in the library dir:</p>

<pre class="literal">
find . -name '*.php' -print0 | xargs -0 grep -P '@param[ ]+\$'
</pre>

<p>The main side effect is that IDEs are generally be unable to do correct code completion/hinting for these methods.</p>

    </div>
